comments.body:
@mheon 

I am killing podman containers from inside the container and these containers are systemd-based. My concern is to understand what is the minimum version of systemd is required to pass `kill -RTMIN+13` from inside the container to make sure the container will exit.

I think podman is doing its job but it is mainly systemd that performs immediate halt so I need to make sure my containers must have the correct systemd version.
